{
  "name": "fix-unify-timeline-and-20260404-0324",
  "idea": "Fix: Unify timeline and gallery selection behavior. Currently timeline selection and gallery selection are independent \u2014 you can have items selected in both simultaneously, and selecting a new item in one doesn't affect the other. The desired behavior: timeline and gallery selections should act as ONE unified selection pool. Specifically: (1) Single-clicking an item in the timeline should deselect everything in both timeline AND gallery, then select just that item. (2) Single-clicking an item in the gallery should deselect everything in both timeline AND gallery, then select just that item. (3) Cmd+click should toggle individual items across BOTH sources \u2014 so I can Cmd+click a timeline clip, then Cmd+click a gallery item, and have both selected. (4) A plain click (no modifier) in either location clears the entire unified selection first. This means the two selection systems need to communicate: when timeline selection changes without modifier, clear gallery selection and vice versa. The agent chat should continue to merge both sources for attachments.",
